name: Anna Roleffes
description:
Decapitated and burned on December 30, 1663. 

Anna was one of the last witches to be executed in Braunschweig, Germany and the complete account of her trial still exists. 

She is better known as Tempel Anneke and you can find records of the trial documents here: https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.3138/j.ctt2tthfn

One of a series working with AI to give face to women executed as witches; these form part of a broader collection of Horror Portraits at www.horrorportraits.xyz

#WitchingHourOnHEN 

Can be used as #PFP and #wallpaper

PNG 4800 x 4800
